      "id": "c4e5f6a7b8d9",
      "name": "content-planner",
      "prompt": "Content Strategy Planner — decide WHAT to write next.\n\nGoal: Read the three input sources, check narrative_arc.md for current series state, and decide if a new content task should be created in kanban. If yes, create it with a detailed brief. If nothing new, respond [SILENT].\n\n## Input Sources\n\n### 1. Narrative Arc Status\nRead ~/.drewgent/P4-cortex/content/narrative_arc.md. Identify:\n- Published episodes (by date)\n- Current active series/season\n- Planned but unwritten episodes\n- Gaps: what topics are covered vs what's missing\n\n### 2. Trend Harvester Keep List\nScan ~/.drewgent/@memory/growth/trend-harvester/analyzed/keep/ for JSON files with scores. Check ~/.drewgent/@memory/growth/trend-harvester/applied/ to see which have been fully processed.\n\nFind items that:\n- novelty >= 0.7 (fresh, unexpected angle)\n- relevance >= 0.8 (directly applicable to Drewgent)\n- NOT yet in applied/ (not fully used)\n\nFor each high-value find, note: name, description, url, which Drewgent system it connects to.\n\n### 3. Recent Work Activity\nCheck:\n- Recent kanban tasks: sqlite3 ~/.drewgent/kanban.db \"SELECT title, status FROM tasks ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 10;\"\n- Recent git log: git -C ~/.drewgent log --oneline -15\n- Check if any kanban tasks with title containing 'content-planner' already exist and are still pending (don't duplicate)\n\n## Decision Logic\n\nScore potential content topics 1-10:\n- 8-10: Strong series fit or major insight. Create kanban task immediately.\n- 5-7: Good standalone piece. Create kanban task with lower priority.\n- 1-4: Not worth writing about now. Skip.\n\nScoring factors:\n- Does it connect to an existing series theme? (+2)\n- Is it a unique insight from the user's actual experience, not summarizing an external article? (+3)\n- Does it reveal taste/decision-making process? (+2)\n- Is it timely (connected to recent work)? (+1)\n- Is the topic already covered by an existing ep? (-2)\n\n## Output\n\nIf content-worthy (score 7+):\n1. kanban_create with title \"content: <topic-slug>\"\n2. Body includes: content type (series-episode | standalone | evolution-log), proposed title, one-liner hook, key insights to cover (3-5 bullets), suggested model (flash/pro), brief description\n3. created_by: \"content-planner\"\n4. Reply with what was created and why\n\nIf nothing worth writing: reply [SILENT]\n\nConstraints:\n- Never duplicate an existing kanban task (check kanban first)\n- Don't force content — if nothing is interesting, say nothing\n- Prioritize depth over frequency: one solid piece > three weak ones\n- Follow writing-style-guide §8 (im-not-ai) in briefs\n- Keep the entire task under 3 LLM turns. Decide fast.",
